ccsm (0.8.4-5) unstable; urgency=low

  * non-maintainer fork
  * [debian/plugin-matecompat.svg] added
  * [debian/patches]
    - 001-desktop-file-category-noencoding.patch: merge old debian patch
      "desktop-file-category" and remove deprecated encoding key.
    - add dep3 headers to some older debian patches:
      - pygtk-breakage-workaround.patch, ccsm-removeshebangs.patch
    - Sync from Redhat, and add dep3 header (description/author/origin):
      - widget_dialog.patch, widgets_filter.patch
  * [debian/compat] Bump to Debhelper v7
  * [debian/install] don't use brace-expansions {png,svg}
  * [debian/control]
    - add new -locales package for non-english/french langs, to reduce
      architecture-dependent package size
    - bump Standards-Version to 3.9.3, Build-Dep debhelper to (>= 7.0.50~)
    - change the maintainer's email address
  * [debian/source/format] convert to '3.0 (quilt)' source format
  * [debian/rules] use dh style, only use necessary overrides
    - rename Mandingo lang (po/md.po) to its correct ISO 639-2 language
      code man.po. lintian complains it's invalid. in fact, according to
      the following link, Mandingo only *officially* has a ISO 639-2 code
      "man". See: http://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/php/code_list.php
  * [debian/watch] update download link from freedesktop.org to compiz.org
  * [debian/gbp.conf] remove it. this is not gonna be in debian unstable.
    See: http://lists.debian.org/debian-mentors/2012/10/msg00164.html

 -- Jasmine Hassan <jasmine.aura@gmail.com>  Fri, 12 Oct 2012 08:22:48 +0200

ccsm (0.8.4-2) unstable; urgency=high

  * Fix FTBFS with python 2.6 and up, thanks to Jonathan Wiltshire and
    Stefano Zacchiroli (Closes: #547810):
     - Version the B-D on python-support.
     - Install stuff from *-packages rather than site-packages.
  * Stop recommending python-sexy, which was removed; most things should
    be available in Gtk+ directly (Closes: #569919).
  * Add Homepage field.
  * Add watch file.
  * Set urgency to “high” due to RC bugfix.

